00:38:28.059 --> 00:38:30.350
Do you want to-- are you
speaking in a business context

00:38:30.350 --> 00:38:31.209
or social?

00:38:31.209 --> 00:38:32.750
AUDIENCE: I think
it applies to both.

00:38:32.750 --> 00:38:33.960
So I'd be curious--

00:38:33.960 --> 00:38:35.210
ANDREW HORN: Yeah, absolutely.

00:38:35.210 --> 00:38:36.602
So let's start with social.

00:38:36.602 --> 00:38:38.060
And this is something
that I've had

00:38:38.060 --> 00:38:40.700
to come to grips with
as well, is again,

00:38:40.700 --> 00:38:42.824
dealing with my own
anxieties and shyness

00:38:42.824 --> 00:38:44.240
with social
interaction, and how I

00:38:44.240 --> 00:38:46.230
wanted to show up in the world.

00:38:46.230 --> 00:38:48.770
One thing that I've become
very clear on later in life

00:38:48.770 --> 00:38:51.830
is that it is not
our responsibility

00:38:51.830 --> 00:38:54.290
to make people feel comfortable.

00:38:54.290 --> 00:38:57.749
It is our responsibility
to be honest to ourselves.

00:38:57.749 --> 00:38:59.540
And this is within the
construct of, again,

00:38:59.540 --> 00:39:02.180
leading with kindness, is
that we cannot harm people,

00:39:02.180 --> 00:39:03.560
so we need to lead
with kindness.

00:39:03.560 --> 00:39:06.056
But that ultimately, it
is not our responsibility

00:39:06.056 --> 00:39:07.180
to make people comfortable.

00:39:07.180 --> 00:39:10.560
It is our responsibility to
be honest with ourselves.

00:39:10.560 --> 00:39:12.980
And if we're accepting of
some of these principles

00:39:12.980 --> 00:39:16.220
about asking questions
and knowing who we are

00:39:16.220 --> 00:39:20.450
and being fully present,
I think that sometimes you

00:39:20.450 --> 00:39:22.460
are going to
interact with people

00:39:22.460 --> 00:39:25.040
who don't connect with you,
who are not on your frequency.

00:39:25.040 --> 00:39:28.790
And I think that knowing that
you've showed up in integrity

00:39:28.790 --> 00:39:32.510
in those moments as yourself
allows you to not get

00:39:32.510 --> 00:39:35.110
hung up on them, allows
you to move forward.

00:39:35.110 --> 00:39:37.610
And the reality is that
you only have limited time

00:39:37.610 --> 00:39:39.920
on this Earth, and
so those people who

00:39:39.920 --> 00:39:42.749
aren't able to meet
you where you're at

00:39:42.749 --> 00:39:44.540
are oftentimes not
those people that you're

00:39:44.540 --> 00:39:45.456
going to connect with.

00:39:45.456 --> 00:39:49.310
You know, I'd say that, again,
in the professional context,

00:39:49.310 --> 00:39:53.300
seeking to understand people
is this virtuous path where

00:39:53.300 --> 00:39:55.940
if people aren't going to
meet you all the way at what's

00:39:55.940 --> 00:39:58.550
your dream, and you're
meeting them at--

00:39:58.550 --> 00:40:00.650
whether it's like Penn
Station or whatever it is--

00:40:00.650 --> 00:40:02.570
I think that there's
a way that you can

00:40:02.570 --> 00:40:04.980
start earlier on to get there.

00:40:04.980 --> 00:40:07.760
And so again, I think that just
because someone can't meet you

00:40:07.760 --> 00:40:09.719
there, like, if you were
to break down again--

00:40:09.719 --> 00:40:12.260
and you talked about, when we
were chatting right here, like,

00:40:12.260 --> 00:40:14.610
your perception of
people right off the bat.

00:40:14.610 --> 00:40:18.470
And I love the idea that
your first question is not

00:40:18.470 --> 00:40:19.970
your real question.

00:40:19.970 --> 00:40:22.130
It's that for a lot
of people, like, they

00:40:22.130 --> 00:40:24.266
won't be able to go
there right off the bat.

00:40:24.266 --> 00:40:25.640
So what is another
question right

00:40:25.640 --> 00:40:27.890
after that that you can go into?

00:40:27.890 --> 00:40:30.380
And again, just allowing
yourself to lead with curiosity

00:40:30.380 --> 00:40:32.213
and what you want to
know about that person.

00:40:32.213 --> 00:40:34.910
So if they're not willing
to talk about their dreams

00:40:34.910 --> 00:40:39.020
or what they care about, what
do you want to know about them,

00:40:39.020 --> 00:40:41.150
and why they're not
willing to go there?

00:40:41.150 --> 00:40:43.280
It's, again, just giving
yourself to that process

00:40:43.280 --> 00:40:44.904
and seeing where that
takes you I think

00:40:44.904 --> 00:40:47.555
is always going to
be a virtuous path.

00:40:47.555 --> 00:40:48.430
Does that make sense?

00:40:48.430 --> 00:40:49.545
AUDIENCE: Yeah Thank you.

